INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11111,'runes','These brightly glowing runes are etched into the red metal walls, floor\nand ceiling.  They are completely foreign to your eyes.  As you look at\nthem they seem to crawl around on the wall.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11112,'runes','These brightly glowing runes are etched into the red metal walls, floor\nand ceiling.  They are completely foreign to your eyes.  As you look at\nthem they seem to crawl around on the wall.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11112,'spec dust','This tiny spec of dust seems out of place here.  When you move to get a\ncloser look you hear voices coming from below.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11170,'ropes','These glowing red ropes vibrate with power.  No force in the universe is\nstrong enough to break them.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11190,'bottles','Large bottles line this wall.   They are filled with various organs and\nappendages of many of the guest of the Ryoken.  As you look you notice\none jar full of eyeballs.  The eyeballs are all looking at you and watching\nyou move about the room.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11191,'poles','These tall red metal poles have been rigged to vibrate with every step\nyou take.  However, you discover this only after stomping on the floor a\nfew times.  The lack of blood from the victims impaled on the pales draws\nyour attention.  Despite your detailed search you are unable to find out\nwhy there is no blood on the poles.  The subjects impaled on the poles\nask you to leave as quickly as possible.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11193,'elf','A once proud elven warrior has been strapped spread eagle on the table.\nThe skin has been flayed of more than a quarter of his body.  Small clamps\nhave been placed on various exposed blood vessels causing them to swell to\nenormous size.  A subtle movement in his chest alerts you to the fact that\nhe is still alive.  As you marvel at the skill of his torturer you hear him\nwhisper, \"Ki..l...kill..m..me....pl..ple...pleas....please....\"\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11193,'ogre','A huge hulking ogre sits in the corner whimpering like a kicked puppy.  His\nclothing and the fact that his hands have been cut off identify him as an\nex-thief.  Thick metal spikes have been driven through his shoulders and\nknees.  His teeth have been pulled out and shoved into his forehead to create\na cavity filled crown.  One of his eyes hang out of its socket.  He doesn\'t\nseem to notice you, how rude.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11193,'halfling','A halfling hangs from the ceiling like a punching bag.  His clothing\nidentifies him as a former mage.  Heavy metal weights have been attached\nto his body by hooks.  The weights have been placed at strategic points\nto help him grow taller.  Maybe someday he\'ll be a big boy.  Tears of\njoyful anticipation cloud his eyes.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11194,'eyes','A pair of beady, red eyes glare back at you.  A small gnome sits in the\nlarge steel cage.  When you don\'t look away the gnome spits at you and\nshouts, \"What\'re you looking at?  Ain\'t you never seen a gnome in a cage\n\'efore?  Get out of here before I call the guards and they put you in a\ncage too.!\"\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11195,'charts','These charts are made out of the hides of paladins of various races.  Most\nof them describe various types of tortures and the best ways to visit them\nupon an unfortunate subject.  The ink on the charts is made of sparkling\nhalfling blood that remains as fresh as the day the charts were drawn.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11195,'carpet','This luxurious red carpet covers the entire floor.  You notice a niche\nhas been cut out of the carpet.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11195,'niche','The niche marks the place of a trap door.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11196,'table','This is a huge red table.  On the table are over one hundred items that\ncan be used for self torture.  They all show signs of recent use.\nEverything from barbed flogging whips to thumb screws can be found here.\nYou may feel free to experiment upon yourself and your loved ones at any\ntime.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11197,'sign','Written in fine gold letters is the following message.\nCaution:  The room to the south is the INCINERATOR room.\nThat room is used to help our guests leave their worldly burdens behind.\nIf you wish to leave, south is the surest way.\n\nRyoken Master Torturer\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11199,'walls','The walls of this room are made out of an exotic metal, the likes of which\nyou have never seen.  On the east wall, behind a tapestry, is a large door.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11208,'crystal','As you look through the door and into the room beyond you see a large\nroom with two huge tables and many strange looking devices laying on the\ntables.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11213,'crystal','When you look through the door into the room beyond you see dozens of\nhumanoid bodies stacked one atop the other.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11230,'bowl','This is apparently the bed of the High Lord.  It appears to be full of\nastral energies that shift about when you touch them.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11231,'throne','This huge throne is made up of the souls of the dead and a strange red\nmetal that appears to trap them within.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11234,'vine','This vine looks strangely like a rope.  You follow the vine to a concealed\ndoor.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11237,'grate','This is a large grate down which blood and gore seems to be flowing.\nIt looks large enough for a man to maybe crawl around in.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11300,'brush','The brush is short scrub with leaves that do not change color, regardless\nof season.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11301,'boot print','The boot-prints seem to be recent impressions in the dust.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11301,'twigs branches','The twigs and branches are not interesting.  They are dead parts from trees.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11302,'brush plant','The brush is short scrub with leaves that do not change color, regardless\nof season.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11303,'rock outcropping','  As you walk around to the back of the rock outcropping, a hole affording\npassage to the interior is visible.  Perhaps if you tried to open up the\nhole a bit, you might fit through.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11303,'scrub','The brush is tall scrub with leaves that do not change color, regardless\nof season.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11304,'hole','The hole appears to connect this room with the outside world.  Perhaps you\ncould make it bigger and then you might fit through it.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11305,'shards rock','The shards are sharp and you will prick your finger if you examine too closely.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11306,'walls bloodstains','Well, let\'s see.  Yep, definitely type O, but you just can\'t tell the Rh\nfactor without more visual acuity.  Perhaps if you had more light?\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11310,'walls gashes','The walls are completely exhausted of riches.  You aren\'t going to find any\nmore by looking now.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11312,'wooden posts','The posts are falling apart and you wisely decide not to examine them further.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11313,'wall blockade granite','There is a sluice set into the wall.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11326,'boulders','The boulders are far too heavy to move - it is truly impassable.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11328,'hut','The hut is small and sturdy, and has a small door which you may reach.\nCuriously, it is sunk into the ground in such a way so that the back wall\nof the hut is flush with the crevice floor as it meets the rock barrier.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11328,'door','The door is accessible at the front of the hut.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11329,'door','Open, the door provides access to the out of doors.  Shut, it offers\nsecurity and increased thermal efficiency of the heating and cooling\nsystems of the hut.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11330,'walls granite','The walls are not interesting, they are only solid rock.  The\nonly light fixture about the room is firmly attached to the rock\nwall and seems to be angled at a family portrait immortalized on\nthe rock.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11330,'portrait family','Quite a homely looking family.  A thin crack is just barely visible\nabout the edges of the portrait.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11330,'crack','It appears the portrait is actually painted on a moveable section\nof the wall.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11331,'roof hut','The roof of the hut appears easy to walk up.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11339,'door rune','The door has an ancient rune inscribed upon it.  You do not know what it means.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11340,'door','The door is sturdy and looks very, very old.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11343,'door rune gigantic','The door is made of solid rock and is very large.  A rune adorns the face\nof the door in bas-relief.  You do not recognize any features of the rune\nsave that it is extremely large.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11344,'door','The door is made of solid rock and is very large.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11345,'granite wall','There is a sluice set into the wall.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11346,'walls','The walls no longer contain anything of value, unless you consider earth\nto be valuable.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11348,'shore pebbles','It\'s a small shore of pebbles, nothing more.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11369,'boulder','The boulder is very large.  It may even be the one that a deity created when a\nsnickering antipaladin confronted him with the question, \"can you create a\nboulder so big that even you cannot lift it?\"  It is rumored that the deity\ntook a thousand year sabbatical after that.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11375,'pile','The pile is comprised of earth, rock and splinters of wooden posts.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11377,'pile debris','The pile is comprised of earth, rock and splinters of wooden posts.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11388,'rune wall northwest','Carved deeply into the rock itself and painted with a shimmering\nblack chalky substance the rune has no meaning for you.  What does\ncatch your eye is that the rune is almost perfectly centered on a\nslab of rock surrounded by a crack basically rectangular in shape.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11389,'chink','It\'s a chink in the ceiling.  What, did you think you could open it or something?\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11390,'pile dirt rocks','You search the pile of dirt and rocks for at least an hour.  You don\'t find\nanything, so you search it again.  Fortunately you then come to your senses\nand stop searching.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11395,'bridge','The bridge is particularly flimsy, and you might not successfully cross it.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11396,'rope knotted','The knotted rope holding the very framework of the bridge together is\ncoming apart, strand by strand.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11397,'bridge','The bridge is particularly flimsy, and you might not successfully cross it.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11398,'pile','The rotting pile of refuse is the most disgusting thing you have seen in\nyour entire life.  The odor is singularly the most intense experience your\nnose has had in its entire life.  Perhaps it is a sophisticated last-resort\ndefense for the leader of the demi-human forces here.  Or maybe it is just\nthat Balrogs have the most disgusting eating and hygiene habits of any creature\nyou\'ve ever encountered before.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11410,'door steel','It\'s a very strong looking steel door.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11414,'blood stains','The bloodstains on the floor are evidence of the effort that the trainees\nput forth to stay in top condition.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11420,'wall granite','There is a large crack in the solid granite wall.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11420,'crack','The crack has a large edges you may be able to grasp and widen.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11420,'edges','The edges of the crack are large and may be able to be moved.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11420,'rock walls','The walls have been totally stripped of any valuables - you are unlikely to\nfind anything worth keeping now.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11421,'edges','The edges of the crack offer some leverage with which you might be able to\nforce open a passage.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11421,'crack','The crack in the wall allows air to flow through.  Perhaps you could grab\nonto the edges of the crack and widen it.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11421,'wall granite','As you look at the wall, you feel a slight draft from one side.  Upon closer\ninspection, you discover a small crack from which the air emanates.  Perhaps\nyou could grab onto the edges of the crack and widen it.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11424,'fire furnace','It\'s hot.  Newbie hint:  fingers stay far away from fire.\n',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO `roomextra` VALUES (11424,'pots pans knives','The kitchen implements belong to the kitchen.  I think that the deity of\nculinary blessing would be most upset with you if you tampered with this, the\nfinal link in the food chain.\n',NULL,NULL);
